---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions — Dave Sharp Auction">
  <header class="bar">
    <a class="bar-mark" href="/">
      Dave Sharp
      <span>Live Auction</span>
    </a>
    <a class="bar-back" href="/">&larr; Back to the auction</a>
  </header>

  <main class="legal">
    <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
    <div class="updated">Last updated &mdash; May 2026</div>

    <p>
      These terms govern the live auction at <strong>auction.davesharp.art</strong>
      (&ldquo;the auction&rdquo;), run by Dave Sharp (&ldquo;we&rdquo;,
      &ldquo;us&rdquo;). By registering and placing a bid you agree to them, so
      please read them before you bid.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Registration and eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      To bid you must register with your name and a valid email address (a phone
      number is optional) and verify your email using the one-time code we send
      you. You must be 18 or over and able to enter into a binding contract. We may
      decline or remove a registration at our reasonable discretion.
    </p>

    <h2>2. The auction</h2>
    <p>
      The auction is a live ascending auction for a single original painting,
      described on the auction page. It runs between the published opening and
      closing times. The painting is an original, one-of-a-kind work by Dave Sharp,
      signed by the artist, and is described in good faith — colours and detail may
      vary slightly from how images appear on your screen.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Bidding</h2>
    <p>
      Bidding is open only while the auction is live. Each bid must be at least one
      minimum increment above the current bid, and no bid may exceed the published
      maximum bid.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Every bid is binding.</strong> Placing a bid is a commitment to buy
      the painting at that amount if you are the highest bidder when the auction
      closes. Bids cannot be changed or withdrawn once placed.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Closing and anti-snipe</h2>
    <p>
      The auction closes at the published time, except that any bid placed in the
      final 10 minutes extends the closing time by a further 10 minutes. This
      repeats until a 10-minute period passes with no further bids. The highest
      valid bid at the moment the auction closes wins.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Payment</h2>
    <p>
      The winning bidder is notified by email and sent an invoice.
      <strong>Payment in full is due within 24 hours of that invoice.</strong> If
      payment is not received within 24 hours, we may treat the bid as withdrawn and
      offer the painting to the next-highest bidder, who is then subject to the same
      terms — and so on, if necessary.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Delivery</h2>
    <p>
      The winning bid is for the painting only. Delivery or collection is arranged
      separately with the buyer after payment and is at the buyer&rsquo;s cost. We
      will help arrange suitable delivery, but the cost of shipping, packing and any
      insurance is the buyer&rsquo;s responsibility.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Our rights</h2>
    <p>
      We may, at our reasonable discretion, decline or cancel a registration, void a
      bid, remove a bidder, or correct an obvious error in a bid or in the auction
      listing. We may also extend, pause or, in exceptional circumstances, withdraw
      the auction. We would only do these things where it is necessary — for example
      where we suspect fraud, bid manipulation, non-payment, or a breach of these
      terms.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Technical issues</h2>
    <p>
      The auction runs online and depends on systems and connections outside our
      control. We are not responsible for a bid that fails to reach us, or for a
      bidder being unable to bid, because of an interruption to the internet, a
      device, or a third-party service. Nothing in these terms limits our liability
      where it cannot be limited by law.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Your information</h2>
    <p>
      We handle the personal information you give us in line with our
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms, and any auction conducted under them, are governed by the laws of
      England and Wales and subject to the courts of England and Wales.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes and contact</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms from time to time; the version published here is the
      one that applies. Questions about these terms or the auction:
      <a href="mailto:auction@davesharp.art">auction@davesharp.art</a>.
    </p>

    <a class="back" href="/">&larr; Back to the auction</a>
  </main>

  <footer class="foot">
    <span class="foot-links">
      <a href="/terms">Terms &amp; conditions</a>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy</a>
    </span>
    <span>&copy; {year} Dave Sharp &middot; <a href="mailto:auction@davesharp.art">auction@davesharp.art</a></span>
    <span style="margin-left: auto; text-align: right;">Site by &mdash; <a href="https://www.halfgreybear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: none;">HALF GREY BEAR</a></span>
  </footer>
</Layout>
